CatDescriptText: Dedication stone in church reads "Tabernacle Baptist Church, organized April 29, 1874, destroyed by fire Dec. 22, 1936, rebuilt by its members in 1943, dedicated Dec. 19, 1943, Rev. L. G. McLeod, pastor."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of six men wearing suits, including man on right wearing striped double breasted suit with one jacket button fastened, abstract patterned tie, and eyeglasses, standing on steps in front of Tabernacle Baptist Church, 1240 Buena Vista Street, Northside
